{"cursor":"4122","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Location map|Canada Nova Scotia |width=220 |lon_dir=W|lat_dir=N |lat_deg = 45\n|lat_min = 51 |lat_sec = 49.44 |lon_deg = 61 |lon_min = 54 |lon_sec = 33.57\n|caption = Ballantyne's Cove in Nova Scotia }} 'Ballantyne's Cove' {{cite web\n | url = http://www4.nrcan.gc.ca/earth-sciences/geography-boundary/geographical-\n | name/search/unique.php?output=xml&id=CABKW title = Geographical Names of\n | Canada - Ballantynes Cove accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}} {{cite web\n | url = https://gis8.nsgc.gov.ns.ca/scripts/esrimap.dll?name=nsplacenames&cmd=-\n | 4&zoomcons=1&action=zoomToPlace&objid=876&prov=false title = Nova Scotia\n | Geographical Names Database entry for \"Ballantynes Cove (Community),\n | Antigonish County\" (includes map) publisher = Government of Nova Scotia\n | accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}} is a community in Antigonish County, Nova Scotia, Canada, lying on\nBallantynes Cove (Nova Scotia), at the north-western end of St. George's Bay.\n\nBallantyne's Cove, Cape George and Livingstone Cove encompass the area locally\ndesignated as \"The Cape.\" {{cite web\n | url = http://tunatowncharters.com/Directions_to_wharf.html title =\n | Ballantyne's Cove - Directions to wharf publisher = Tuna Town Charters\n | accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}}\n\n\nThe community and cove are named for one of its early settlers, David\nBallantyne, a lowland Scotchman and British soldier who served in the 82nd\nregiment during the American Revolution and who received a grant for military\nservice. {{cite web\n | url = http://www.gov.ns.ca/nsarm/virtual/places/page.asp?ID=32 title = Place-\n | Names and Places of Nova Scotia (1967) publisher = Public Archives of Nova\n | Scotia accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}} He settled in the area around 1810, taking up 1000 acres of land on the\nsouth side of the cape. He died in 1840. {{cite web\n | url = https://gis8.nsgc.gov.ns.ca/scripts/esrimap.dll?name=nsplacenames&cmd=-\n | 4&zoomcons=1&action=zoomToPlace&objid=46532&prov=false title = Nova Scotia\n | Geographical Names Database entry for \"Ballantynes Cove (Cove), Antigonish\n | County\" (includes map) publisher = Government of Nova Scotia accessdate = May\n | 13, 2012\n}}\n\nBallantyne's Cove has a port {{cite web\n | url = http://www.dfo-mpo.gc.ca/sch-ppb/maps/map-eng.asp?p=ns&lat=45.8587&long=-\n | 61.9186 title = Map - Ballantynes Cove (McNair's Cove) publisher = Fisheries\n | and Oceans Canada accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}} (a principal trading point for Japanese merchants looking for sushi-\ngrade Atlantic bluefin tuna) {{cite web\n | url = http://www.xaverianweekly.ca/accounts/20/articles/37099 title =\n | Atlantic bluefin tuna - Ballantyne's Cove publisher = The Xaverian Weekly\n | accessdate = May 13, 2012\n}} that hosts a 40 slip marina and the Ballantyne's Cove Tuna Interpretive\nCentre as well as Ballantyne's Cove Beach.\n","linknr":128,"url":"Ballantynes_Cove,_Nova_Scotia","recorded":1375077069,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Ballantynes_Cove&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Ballantynes_Cove&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Ballantynes_Cove","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Ballantynes_Cove,_Nova_Scotia&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wi